sub_title: Entrepreneur | Blockchain-to-Retail | Innovator | CEO of QX - Creating Tokens for Retailers, Shopping Centers, and Product Brands
summary:
As the co-founder and CEO of Qpick, I lead a global team of tech experts and innovators to create a blockchain-based retail ecosystem that enabled retail stores, shopping centres, and product brands to provide Web3 experience and loyalty. With 15 years of experience in product management, design, business development, and growth hacking, I have successfully launched and scaled Qpick to become an award-winning technology that has attracted investments from top European investors and accelerators, such as Startupbootcamp, Startup Wise Guys, European Commission, EBRD, Societe Generale Bank Group, and FITR.

My passion for creating and building is driven by a desire to help others succeed and positively impact the tech industry. I am a master networker with a well-established network within the SWG, YTILI, and GES alum networks across Europe and the US. I am known for my ability to recruit top talent and forge million-dollar partnerships. With a competitive spirit honed as an athlete and martial artist, I can stay calm, assess the situation, and make data-driven decisions in high-pressure environments. I am always eager to learn new skills, explore new opportunities, and challenge myself to achieve more.

The project is inspired by the needs of the two main target groups, teachers and students. Macedonia's internationally is ranked in the PISA ranks among the last in comparison to the achievements of 15-year-olds in the world. These tests tested language literacy and knowledge in mathematics and natural sciences for 540 thousand students from 72 countries. 

The ranking gave disappointing results, the Macedonian primary school pupils are fourth from behind. Behind them are only the natives of Kosovo, Algeria, and the Dominican Republic. The best results are from the principals of Singapore, Japan, and Estonia. 

According to TIMSS testing in Macedonia, the Macedonian elementary school students in 2011 also achieved striking results in competition from 42 countries, again fourth from behind. The project was organised from 21-29 April 2014 brought together young motivated youth workers and volunteers from SEE and EU countries, in a 7 days program with the main topic being leaders and promote Leadership.

The aim of this training was to equip participants with new knowledge, skills and attitudes, and active learning methods from which they can benefit on how to become a leader and take action, also by promoting a role model for their peers.

Objectives
- To gain the necessary leadership competencies to adapt to a changing world
-To reflect on participants personal leadership style, values, attitudes, and skills in relation to leading in a diverse world;
- To gain a better understanding of working with young people and to include people with different cultural backgrounds in your team;
-To exchange with other participants the challenges arising from diversity in your own environment and to build a network of exchange;
-To benefit from new knowledge and ideas on how to be more inclusive in your leadership role.

The main topic addressed during the TC were:
• Leadership skills, leaders role, leadership styles •Communication. •Motivation. •Facilitation. •Group dynamics. •Conflict management and styles. • Inter-cultural cooperation. Public speaking skills-conducting a good survey, etc.

The whole training was organized with the use of non - formal education methodology by a rich combination of methods and techniques in order to satisfy the participant’s needs & with the added value of the expertise offered by trainers.
